				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}
$$ {N}_{\mathrm{x}}= TTL/\left(t+u\right)=E/({\varepsilon}_0\ \left(t+u\right))=E/\Delta E, $$
\end{document}

∆E being the energy loss in a unit cell of thickness (t + u). Assuming statistical independence of the crossings, the fluctuations in Nx represent the ‘sampling fluctuations’ σ(E)samp,6.21σ(E)samp/E=σNx/Nx=1/√Nx=√ΔEGeV/EGeV=0.032√ΔEMeV/EGeV=a/√E.\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
