\end{document}

The dominant part of the calorimeter signal is actually not produced by minimum ionizing particles, but rather by the low-energy electrons and positrons crossing the signal planes. Defining the fractional response fR of a given layer “i” as the ratio of energies lost in the active layer and of the sum of active plus passive layers one has6.22fRi=Eactivei/(Eactivei+Epassivei)\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
