Taking into account an energy independent contribution from electronics noise b, and a minimum asymptotic value of the relative energy resolution c (constant term, due for example to inhomogeneities in materials, imperfection of calibrations, …) the energy resolution of a sampling calorimeter is in general written as16.23ΔE/E=a/√E⊕b/E⊕c\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
