\end{document}

This characteristic length λint is the mean free path of high energy hadrons between hadronic collisions and sets the scale for the longitudinal hadronic shower profile. The probability P(z) for a hadron traversing a distance z without undergoing an interaction is therefore P(z) = exp. (−z/λint). The equivalence with the characteristic distance X0 for the electromagnetic cascade is evident. In analogy to the parameterization of electromagnetic showers the longitudinal profile of hadronic showers can be parameterized in the form.6.24dE/dx=cwx/X0α−1exp−bx/X0+1−wx/λα−1exp−dx/λ.\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
